Level Difficulty: Low
Commands Used: openssl
               openssl -> toolkit for TLS/SSL and other stuff, s_client lets it act as a TLS client to connect to a server
Steps: openssl s_client -connect localhost:30001 [connects to port 30001 using a TLS handshake instead of plain nc, since this port expects encrypted traffic - host and port need to be colon separated in one argument, not space separated, or openssl gets confused between the option and a bare target]
